com.phunware.mapping.manager

Class PhunwareMapManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.phunware.mapping.manager.PhunwareMapManager

  • public class PhunwareMapManager
extends Object
    Allows interaction with Phunware's mapping service to easily manage building data on a PhunwareMap, and provides navigation abilities using the supplied metadata. The PhunwareMapManager should generally be an application level singleton, and can be initialized automatically by calling create(Context). To override the mapping server endpoint, to test against the staging environment, for instance, add a metadata entry to your application's manifest with the name phunware-mapping-endpoint. ...
